Text.string: I should have known. Should have seen it coming. This is exactly what I was afraid of...
Incoming transmission!
You're heading to an outpost called Roland's Rest. Vaughn will be there.
Well. That's... taken care of. You... must have questions. I can explain.
Hey, the gold car worked! Anyway, I gotta get back to protecting Roland's Rest, but go save Tannis. Leave no bro behind, bro!
Uh, that's odd—we seem to be having some technical difficulties.
Stop talking about Tannis like she's already dead! There's still time!
We kidnapped your scientist.
If you want to see her alive... heh, it's not gonna happen.
Yeah, 'cause you eat butts!
Skag butts.
Vault Hunter. I know I don't need to say this, but we are not losing anyone else.
It's us! Heh—did you guess?
Cool masks, right? Pre-order bonus.||Ooh, Ty—pledge drive.

So, spoiler. We are crazy close to opening the Great Vault. We found the key, bee-tee-dubs, and it is HUGE! So we need a crap-ton of Eridium to charge it and you know what that means! Pledge drive. And since our followers go apeshit everytime we maim or murder one of you, we put the next one up to a vote.
Would you believe it? Weird scientist was our most requested murder. Beat out annoying robot by just a bit!
Damn it!
Speaking of murder, Carnivora's gettin' hungry! The show's starting soon! And it's gonna be a killer.

Tannis risked everything to keep Tyreen from getting to that Vault Monster. She deserves better than dying for the entertainment of two psychopaths. We're going back to Pandora. Vault Hunter: save her.
The Calypsos mentioned a “Carnivora”. Go find Vaughn. I sent him to an old Crimson Raiders outpost in Devil's Razor. He's been monitoring COV movements, he'll know what's goin' on.

Hi, hello? I'm alive! For now. It seems Eridian professors are like Vault Keys: everyone wants a piece.||Ahem. Gallows humor aside, a rescue would be quite welcome, as I'm to be tortured and killed for the amusement of a crowd. I still have some tricks up my sleeve, but I fear using them would only change the method of my death.
Heyyy, you're back! Reunion! Last time we were all here, I plucked your Firehawk and left her on the ground like a hit-and-run skag. Tch—aww, remember that?
I will get her back. I swear it.
I will not rest until she is safely returned.
We'll get her out, commander. No soldier left behind.
Ah, dammit! I didn't think I'd actually end up liking any of you people!||Yeahhh, I'll save her.
Ahhh, good times. Oh, and then I totally murdered your Siren friend. The blue-haired one? I... can't remember her name. I wanna say Martha? Meg? Ah, whatever. She dead.
And now we kidnapped your science nerd too. You gotta admit, we are super good at taking your shit.
Yeah, your Crimson Thieves' Guild is in tatters and splatters and whatnot.
Gonna be gods soon. Later, bitches!
Hey! Welcome to my new clan, the Pectoral Liberation Alliance! I'm just kidding, go Crimson Raiders! Haha! Remember me? Vaughn?
Anyway, I'm glad you came along. It has been hell defending this place since Troy Calypso snatched our turrets with his crazy powers.||I loved those turrets.
Submit your death-ride for judgment! Only the chosen may enter!

My imminent murder is whipping these cultists into a frenzy. They're delivering Eridium by the armful, screaming my name all the way. I had no idea I was so popular amongst the idiot masses. I suppose you never know where flattery's going to come from.
Press the button, that Carnivora may feed!
Hurry up, you idiots! We gotta melt this thing down before somebody tries to take it!
That Donny, always tryin' to save his hide. Get that golden car before he melts it down!
I knew it! Someone's coming to steal my car! That's the tenth idiot trying to get into Carnivora today! Why's everyone so crazy to get murdered? Never shoulda joined this damn cult.
You ain't taking my gold! Come check my BIG D!
Phew, looks like you got him before he could melt down the car. Grab his keys!
Start the conveyor! Gimme gimme! Yum!
You are chosen! Prepare for your glory in Carnivora!
This monstrosity is slowing down. If you can overheat Carnivora's transmission, it will have to stop for repairs.

You made it to the Splinterlands! All right, Carnivora should still be nearby. The festival moves around Pandora, setting up wherever there's enough crazies to fill the bleachers. They've been camped out here for a while now, so, I guess the sacrifice business must be a-boomin'. You'll, uh, you'll know it when you see it.
This is unacceptable! We're live right now! Crew, get out there and fix this!
The transmission is nearly repaired—you have to make it overheat again!
So very close, my spotlight-hogging Vault Thief, but you can't pull our plug that easily. We're going to sacrifice this heretic one way or another!

Ohhh, that's the sound I love to hear! Our engineers have worked their magic once again! Folks, the Agonizer 9000 is up and running! Vault Thief, you might want to hurry up if you don't wanna miss the show.
Oh, it's like a... cannibal festival.
It looks like a zoo connected to a meat grinder.
Oh, fun. Looks like a murder circus.
Looks like a bloody party! Literally!
Yep! That's the one! A little heads up, though—Carnivora is supes exclusive. Only the most dedicated followers get in, so... you're gonna have to give up your car as an offering.
Vault Hunter... destroy that core. Trust me.
A pitiful death-ride! No ticket, no entry, no glory!
Huh, okay. Well, looks like you're gonna need a super pimp ride in order to get in. Oh! Oh-oh-oh, bro! I heard Big Donny over at the Chop Shop won a golden car in a sweepstakes! So... go steal that!
Of course.
You got this, Vault Hunter! Ya freakin' animal. Go save that science lady!
How could I forget? Those undies are burned into my retinas.
Of course. Your abs are burned into my retinas.
Your scent is as strong as ever, my bandit bro.
How could I forget me bandit bro? Good to see ya!
Tannis...
Aw man, Big Donny joined the cult? I used to hold a candle for him, but I never did get to trim his wick, if you catch my drift. Sex-wise.

Carnivora's the most popular Calypso fan-stream in the galaxy, bro! Pain and Terror take kill requests non-stop in the name of the Calypsos—and of course, high viewer counts. Anyway, I can help you get TO Carnivora, but getting in might be a different story.
Fine, I'll kill you myself!
Now get Carnivora to chase you into the oil! It will get mired in the sands!
No sacrifice for me! I'm gonna hock this thing and get off this planet. Sometimes I think I'm the only one around here with an ounce of sense.
Carnivora is immobilized! Destroy its primary fuel tank to keep it from getting away.
What the hell is happening? Why is nothing working? Terror! Fix this!
My only regret... is being killed.
Go on, grab his keys!
The gold car's up on that crane. You'll have to get it down a'fore you can drive that shaggin' wagon to the festival.
They're gonna kill her if we don't do something!
That is one shiny car. Hop on in and drive it to the festival gate. Enjoy the murder circus, y'all!
Hey, hey, hey! This is a professional gig, Vault Thief! Your big moment! If we're gonna get you in the ring, you're gonna need some entrance music. Pick one!
Don't worry, that gold car's registered at the Catch-A-Ride. It'll still work if you need a new one!
Submit your death ride for—WHOA! That is one pimp-ass ride! Park that thing on my tongue!
I hope you are making progress on my rescue. I can hear sawblades beginning to spin up. I wonder what RPM would be needed to turn human blood into an aerosol on impact? I will keep you updated.
Vault Hunter, Carnivora just started broadcasting across the ECHOnet! The sacrifice is about to begin! Don't let anything get between you and Tannis.

Children of the Vault! Who's ready for a very special livescream? The Agonizer 9000 is all oiled up and ready to kill! We've got some great opening acts for you, but while you prepare to see the Great Vault, we're bringing you behind the scenes with our headliner. Now, Blasphemer Tannis, you're a crazy scientist lady who came from space. What's on your mind?

Oh. I was just admiring this elaborate murder device you've assembled. It's the details—the rusted sheetmetal, the haphazard bevelling, the sheer capacity for taking human lives. I can see you put a lot of yourself into this machine, even hanging from these chains.

You know... it's so great to hear you say that. My partner Terror and I, we're—we're awful proud of the Agonizer 9000 here, and so rarely do we get a true... connoisseur of the homicidal arts here in the studio. Tell you what. I'll swing you closer to the action so you can get a proper view.
Ah, yes, this is perfect. You have my gratitude.
Looks like the COV have been busy on Pandora. That's the way to Devil's Razor, but you're gonna have to smash through.
We got a great lineup today, folks! Our opening act is a bullymong poacher from the Southern Shelf—give it up for Ezekiel Sourbones!
Ezekiel has chosen pneumatic spike traps for his run in the Agonizer 9000. Let's take a look.
Oooh, splat. Good run, Ezekiel! See you in the Great Vault! Followers, send in your Eridium now!

Next up, we've got the Blister Sisters! A couple of local favorites, these gals said they wanted to be chased down by fire-breathing spiderants. And I said to Terror—I said, we have a sacred duty to make these gals' dreams come true. So damn it, we made it happen! Release the spiderants!
Boy. Those spiderants, they love killing humans. And I get it, I get it! Nice soft meat, no exoskeleton, slow running speed. Just a really chompable species, we are, huh?

Ohhh, looks like we've got one Blister Sister down and... ah, there goes the other, cooked by spiderant magma breath. Terror, it's moments like these when I think we might have the greatest job in the world! Folks, there's still time to donate Eridium! The Great Vault beckons!

This next sacrificial lamb comes to us all the way from the war-torn megapolitan planet of Promethea, please welcome to the floor... Hungryyyyy Dave! Now, I can—oh, I think he's making—yeah, I see that now! He's rubbin' his little tummy and pointin' to his mouth. He wants us to know he's hungry! Way to build the brand, Dave.
Hope Dave was hungry for saw blades, because that's what's on the menu!

Followers, we're gonna have more glorious bloodshed in the name of our beloved Calypsos in just few moments. Remember: without your Eridium donations, you might be left behind when we open the Great Vault.
Pretty soon those maniacs are going to run out of their own people to kill. Get Tannis out of there!
Oh! Right, the mission! Okay, Lilith says you're here to save Tannis. Now, if Carnivora has her, you gotta get a move on!
This homicidal ritual is going faster than I had expected. As I said, I still have one trick up my sleeve, but... I'd rather not use it.
Folks, we're nearly to our grand sacrifice, the one you've all been waiting for. The heretic scientist who dared to—
Vault Hunter, the stream just cut off. What's happening down there?
I'd love to take credit, but that delay's not because of me.
It was not me. That delay is because of something else.
Wasn't me. But I'm sure Tannis isn't complaining about the delay.
Wasn't me, but anything that delays them is good news.

Sorry for that, folks. Just a few technical difficulties on our end. Someone must have hanged themselves from the antenna again. But Terror's got us back on the air, and we're just a few glorious deaths away from our grand sacrifice!
Next up, we've got the entire Gillybung Clan being smashed through a fine mesh screen. Smash that kill button, followers!
Ooooh, looks like we've got a late entry today—and viewers, this one's a doozy! You know 'em, you hate 'em, you wanna eat 'em—it's the Vault Thief!
But hey, kid! You can't hit the big time THAT easily. Terror! Let's take this show on the road!
Lilith! Carnivora's a gigantic tank!
Commander, the festival is actually a gigantic tank.
Small update: the bloody festival's driving away!
Yo, Lilith? The festival is driving away.
Tannis is still on board that thing! Run it down!
Who the hell is Carnivora?
Who's Carnivora? I'll crush them.
Who is this Carnivora, and how do I kill them?
Who's this Carnivora, then? I'm already killing him, her, or them in my mind.

Ladies, gentlemen, and every other conceivable point on the graph, you're watching the showdown of a lifetime! On one side, the Vault Thief! On the other, the most terrible machine ever built by human hands: Carnivora!
First rule of showbiz, kid—if you can't keep up, you get left behind in the dust. Terror! Punch it!
I think I've identified this monstrosity's weak points. Despite its bulk, it's very fast—you'll need to destroy its fuel lines if you have any hopes of slowing it down.
Typical! Typical Vault Thief behavior—if you can't win, drag 'em down with you.
Go ahead. Make your observation.
So... you're a super-secret Siren?
You're a Siren too?
You are a Siren.
So you're not just a weirdo. You're also a Siren!

Yes. That is how I have been speaking in your head and charging the Vault Keys. As for my particular powers, I am able to manipulate machines and anything else with a current. It is known as “phaseshifting”. You could call it a gift from a guardian angel.
Folks, we're gonna take a quick break.||—Get this Calypso-forsaken pile of trash running. NOW, you idiots!
Great work, Vault Hunter. Now get on board and save Tannis!
Pull the lever, that Carnivora may feed!
Get the engineers back in here. I want the Agonizer 9000 back up and killing! Now. Now! NOW!
Vault Hunter? I'm running out of time!

If these ARE my final moments, what have I left behind? A thousand half-completed experiments? Countless undiscovered artifacts and unanswered questions. I never found the Eridian homeworld, and now it appears I never will.
Incompetent sweat-weasels! Every minute we aren't killing people, we lose half a million subscribers!||—What's that, Terror?
Terror's given me a great idea. Until we get the Agonizer 9000 working, we're going to broadcast the Vault Thief while they murder our crew! How's THAT for entertainment, huh?!

Vault Thief, good news! I gotta say, our subscribers are LOVING YOU! Now, we may have some, uh... let's call 'em “insurmountable philosophical disagreements”, but if there's one thing I can recognize, it's a certifiable killing machine! The Calypsos were right about you!

If I die, I need you to take care of some unfinished business for me. First, there is a signed poster of Typhon DeLeon in my room on Sanctuary. Give it to Lilith. Second, I have a database of compromising information on rival scientists. Please release it all onto the ECHOnet. And... third...
Hey, hey, hey! Science lady! You look like you're about to fall asleep. You don't want to miss your big moment! Terror—cattle prod.
—kill these sons of bitches!
No, it's not a who—it's a what. Carnivora is a giant festival run by two murderstreamers named Pain and Terror. You can find it in the Splinterlands, bro.
Welcome... to the greatest show on Pandora!
